The paper deals with the problem of quantum communication, specifically entanglement-assisted quantum state redistribution. This falls under the category of quantum information (cs.QI). The paper also uses techniques from information theory, such as the max-relative entropy and hypothesis testing relative entropy, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses convex split and position-based decoding techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of coding theory (cs.CC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the problem of quantum state redistribution can also be seen as a problem in control theory (cs.SY), as it involves manipulating quantum states to achieve a desired outcome.
